{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774384600,"nonce":"EGyOMZdp9yeuyNPKDY57RpGOryU=","title":"Bug: --target-ratio CLI flag has no effect (loss_update never enabled)","message":"build_hps() in train_part2_5.py stores target_ratio from --target-ratio but never sets loss_update.enabled = True. The _loss_cfg_running_cost() (and all other loss config functions) hardcode \"enabled\": False. Without an --enable-loss-update flag, all models are trained with the adaptive control penalty disabled regardless of what --target-ratio is set to.\n\nThis caused the Part 2.5 loss-balance experiment (ratio03_pert1, ratio05_pert1, ratio03_pert10, ratio05_pert10) to train without the adaptive update. The ratio03 and ratio05 models at each pert_std are literally identical (same MD5 hash for trained_model.eqx and train_history.eqx) because target_ratio is irrelevant.\n\nFix: add --enable-loss-update flag to argparser; in build_hps(), set merged[\"loss_update\"][\"enabled\"] = True when this flag is present. The getattr(..., False) fallback handles old configs without the key.","files":null}]}